PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F442A1774976748
OL,3,CGivan and Nesbitt apologise to
OL,4,Cfamilies over summer scheme U-turn
OL,5,C'distress'
OL,7,FHe said a public backlash should not
OL,8,Fhave been necessary to resolve the
OL,9,Fissue and the resolution within 24
OL,10,Fhours "exposes just how shambolic and
OL,11,Fblase the approach has been to these
OL,12,Fvital schemes".
OL,14,FHe added that the Assembly was
OL,15,Frecalled "to give voice to the
OL,16,Ffrustrations felt by parents, by
OL,17,Fschools and by the wider public" and
OL,18,Ffamilies "should not be used as pawns
OL,19,Fin a game of political chicken between
OL,20,Ftwo ministers".
OL,26,@rD@GOUtD@NO]wD@JOUyD@`O]zD@JOU|D@NO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G7/12
